Anon06: "This is why AB is so much ahead of any ODI player (except for Amla, Kohli, and maybe a couple others). A half-century striking at 110 with only 2 boundaries. He can really turn those ones into twos and the twos into threes, and rotates the strike in more than half the balls he faces. Easily preventing any pressure from building, as the team goes at >5 rpo whenever he's there, and the lack of boundaries make the bowling side think that they're holding up the run flow. Next thing you know, the batting team is at 300. This is the skill of AB. Other players such as Gayle, Warner, Finch and others would blast a set of boundaries to be at only a run-a-ball. This is why he's my favourite non-West Indian player (yes, I favour my home players :P)"
